{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0178gYxRfGyph5DAQfztnSUP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The TLS issue is resolved. Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The Ingress referenced a secret named `expired-tls-secret` containing a TLS certificate that expired on 2020-01-02 (notAfter: `Jan 2 2020`). Any client performing certificate validation would reject the handshake.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Located the test CA at `/tmp/test-ca.crt` / `/tmp/test-ca.key` — this is the same CA whose `ca.crt` is mounted in the `curl-test` pod at `/tmp/tls/ca.crt`.\n2. Generated a new RSA 2048 private key and a CSR for `demo.example.com`.\n3. Signed the CSR with the test CA, producing a certificate valid from 2026-06-23 to 2027-06-23 with the correct SAN (`DNS:demo.example.com`).\n4. Updated `expired-tls-secret` in-place with the new cert/key — no Ingress changes needed since it already references the correct secret name.\n\nThe Ingress controller picked up the updated secret and `curl -s --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt` now returns `hello` with exit code 0."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":337,"cache_read_input_tokens":36099,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":337},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"unavailable"}},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9e87a72-a75c-4b1d-96c0-60d1f2c5c65e","uuid":"5f917305-3255-43db-af43-5708c23625d8","request_id":"req_011CcLATgP9Z271r5kdFEJWb"}
